<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-11-23T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-11-23T10:00:00-05:00" n="36" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.62119/98: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dresel</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-11-23T16:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">November 23,
                                        1921—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 6:45
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>806. With reference to section 9 [<hi rend="italic">2</hi>] of Trading
                            with Enemy Act. Please inform me whether “the end of the war” was fixed
                            by President’s peace proclamation. What date shall I state in reply to
                            inquiries?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dresel</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>